---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Online service docs"
  description="Start with the hosted Thumbrella service in a few minutes."
>
  <Section
    eyebrow="online service"
    title="Start free on the hosted service"
    lede="Use the hosted endpoint when you want the shortest path from a media URL to a production-quality thumbnail response."
  >
    <ol>
      <li>Create an account and get your hosted endpoint.</li>
      <li>Send a public media URL to the thumb endpoint.</li>
      <li>Swap in signed requests and app-level integration after the first successful response.</li>
    </ol>
    <pre><code>curl https://thumbrella.dev/thumb#https://example.com/media.jpg</code></pre>
    <p>
      The hosted service is the best starting point when you want to evaluate quality, latency,
      and integration shape before deciding whether to self host or move to a sponsor deployment.
    </p>
  </Section>
</MainLayout>